			Company Description 


			Aboitiz Equity Ventures, Inc. operates as a holding company that engages in management operations of the Aboitiz Group. It operates through the following segments: Power, Banking and Financial Services, Food, Real Estate, and Infrastructure. The Power segment engages in the power generation and sale...
		


                Aboitiz Equity Ventures, Inc. operates as a holding company that engages in management operations of the Aboitiz Group. It operates through the following segments: Power, Banking and Financial Services, Food, Real Estate, and Infrastructure. The Power segment engages in the power generation and sale of electricity. The Food Manufacturing segment produces flour and feeds and handles swine breeding. The Financial Services segment manages the banking and money remittance operations. The Real Estate segment sells and leases real property development. The Infrastructure segment produces cement and other building materials, and supplies treated bulk water. The parent and Other segment includes operations of the company and the service provider subsidiaries that cater to the Group. The company was founded on September 11, 1989 and is headquartered in Taguig, Philippines.
            




