d          Open  0.00   Prior Close  15.04 (03/17/17)     1 Day    ABTZY -5.45%     DJIA 0.47%     S&P 500 0.29%     Business/Consumer Services -0.06%                             Overview Profile     Overview Profile Financials Income Statement Balance Sheet Cash Flow Research & Ratings Historical Prices Options Advanced Charting              Company Info Aboitiz Equity Ventures Inc. ADR        NAC Tower Taguig MM 1634 Philippines   Email Website Map       Employees  -    Sector  Diversified Holding Companies      Sales or Revenue  114.56 B    Industry  Business/Consumer Services      1Y Sales Change   2.97%     Fiscal Year Ends  December 31 Download Reports                      Description Aboitiz Equity Ventures Inc. ADR      Aboitiz Equity Ventures, Inc. operates as a holding company that engages in management operations of the Aboitiz Group. It operates through the following segments: Power, Banking and Financial Services, Food, Real Estate, and Infrastructure. The Power segment engages in the power generation and sale of electricity. The Food Manufacturing segment produces flour and feeds and handles swine breeding. The Financial Services segment manages the banking and money remittance operations. The Real Estate segment sells and leases real property development. The Infrastructure segment produces cement and other building materials, and supplies treated bulk water. The parent and Other segment includes operations of the company and the service provider subsidiaries that cater to the Group. The company was founded on September 11, 1989 and is headquartered in Taguig, Philippines.    expand             Key People Aboitiz Equity Ventures Inc. ADR   Board of Directors    Name/Title Current Board Membership          Jon Ramon Melendez Aboitiz, 59  Chairman   Pilmico Foods Corp., Philippine Business For Social Progress, Bloomberry Resorts Corp., Aboitiz Jebsen Co., Inc., Union Bank of the Philippines, Ramon Aboitiz Foundation, Inc., Aboitiz Power Corp., Internati